# nl-rag distilled facts — domain: 2022-baseball5-world-cup
# one declarative sentence per line; load with:  neuron --db app.db import pack.facts --scope knowledge
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/2020-baseball5-european-championship] The **2020 Baseball5 European Championship** was an international baseball5 tournament organized by the WBSC Europe.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/2020-baseball5-european-championship] The championship was held from 28 February to 1 March 2020, in Vilnius, Lithuania and was contested between 14 national teams.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/2020-baseball5-european-championship] France won the tournament, beating Lithuania in the final 2 matches to 0.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/2020-baseball5-european-championship] Russia finished third defeating Italy 2 matches to 0 in the Bronze medal game.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/2022-baseball5-african-championship] The **2022 Baseball5 African Championship** was the first edition of the Baseball5 African Championship, a Baseball5 tournament organized by WBSC Africa.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/2022-baseball5-african-championship] The championship was held from 23 to 26 May 2022, in the Tanzania National Indoor Stadium in Dar es Salaam, Tanzania and was contested between ten national teams.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/2022-baseball5-african-championship] South Africa won the tournament, defeating Kenya in the final 2 matches to 0.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/2022-baseball5-african-championship] Tunisia finished third beating Uganda 2 matches to 0 in the bronze medal game.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/2022-baseball5-african-championship] South Africa and Kenya automatically qualified to the 2022 Baseball5 World Cup held in Mexico City, while Tunisia was given a wild card spot in the world tournament by the World Baseball Softball Confederation.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/2022-baseball5-asia-cup] The **2022 Baseball5 Asia Cup** was the first edition of the Baseball5 Asia Cup, a Baseball5 tournament organized by WBSC Asia.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/2022-baseball5-asia-cup] The championship was held from 16 to 19 August 2022, in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia and was contested between nine national teams.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/2022-baseball5-asia-cup] Chinese Taipei won the tournament, beating Japan in the final 2 matches to 1.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/2022-baseball5-asia-cup] South Korea finished third defeating Hong Kong 2 matches to 0 in the Bronze medal game.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/2022-baseball5-world-cup] The **2022 Baseball5 World Cup** was the first edition of the Baseball5 World Cup, the mixed-gender Baseball5 (B5) world championship organized by the World Baseball Softball Confederation (WBSC).
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/2022-baseball5-world-cup] It was held in Mexico City from 7 to 12 November 2022.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/2022-baseball5-world-cup] Cuba won the tournament, beating Japan in the final 2 matches to 0.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/2022-baseball5-world-cup] Chinese Taipei finished third defeating Venezuela 2 matches to 0 in the bronze medal game.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/2022-baseball5-world-cup] 1There was no qualification event for WBSC Americas and WBSC Oceania.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/2022-baseball5-world-cup] Teams were selected by World Baseball Softball Confederation.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/2022-baseball5-world-cup] 2In October 2022, WBSC chose Hong Kong to replace Australia.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/2024-baseball5-world-cup] The **2024 Baseball5 World Cup** was the second edition of the Baseball5 World Cup, the mixed-gender Baseball5 (B5) world championship organized by the World Baseball Softball Confederation (WBSC).
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/2024-baseball5-world-cup] It was held in Hong Kong from 7 to 12 October 2024.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/2024-baseball5-world-cup] The tournament was won by Cuba in their second straight Baseball5 World Cup title.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/2024-baseball5-world-cup] The Cuban team defeated Japan in the championship game, a replay of the 2022 final, 2 sets to 0 to finish the tournament undefeated with a 9–0 record.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/2024-baseball5-world-cup] Cuban players Briandy Molina and Haila González received the Male MVP and Female MPV of the World Cup.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/2024-baseball5-world-cup] France claimed the bronze after defeating Venezuela in the bronze medal game, 2 sets to 0.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/2024-baseball5-world-cup] The 2024 World Cup cost $12 million to host, with the Baseball Association of Hong Kong providing half of the funding.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/2024-baseball5-world-cup] The event has been given "M" Mark status (major sport event) by the Hong Kong government.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/australia-national-baseball5-team] The **Australia national Baseball5 team** represents Australia in international Baseball5 competitions.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/australia-national-baseball5-team] Australia was scheduled to take part in the inaugural Baseball5 World Cup held in Mexico City in November 2022, but the team did not participate and was replaced by Hong Kong less than one month before the beginning of the tournament.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/australia-national-baseball5-team] Australia made its Baseball5 World Cup debut in 2024 in Hong Kong.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/australia-national-baseball5-team] Trials were held in Victoria, New South Wales and Queensland to determine the squad that would play in the World Cup.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/australia-national-baseball5-team] Australia debuted with two defeats on the first day of the tournament against Mexico and Japan.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/australia-national-baseball5-team] The team finished last in Group B in the Opening Round, losing their remaining games against China, Tunisia and France.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5-world-cup] The **Baseball5 World Cup** (**B5WC**, and sometimes referred to as the **Senior Baseball5 World Cup**) is a mixed-gender Baseball5 (B5) world championship that occurs every two years, with the first edition held in 2022 in Mexico and contested by 12 countries.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5-world-cup] It is governed by the World Baseball Softball Confederation (WBSC).
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5-world-cup] The inaugural B5WC was originally planned to happen in December 2020 in Mexico.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5-world-cup] The COVID-19 pandemic led to the delay of the B5WC to June 2021; however, the continued impact of the pandemic delayed the B5WC further.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5-world-cup] It was later decided that the WC would be played every two years, starting in 2022.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5-world-cup] The 14-team 2020 European Baseball5 Championship held in February and March saw France and Lithuania take the two available Europe berths to qualify for the inaugural B5WC.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5-world-cup] The Oceania qualifier was scheduled to be played in Australia in 2021.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5-world-cup] The Asia qualifiers were scheduled to be played in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia in April 2021, but were then postponed due to COVID-19 to August 17–19, 2022.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5-world-cup] The first edition of the tournament, held in Mexico City, was won by Cuba, who finished the championship undefeated.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5-world-cup] In April 2023, it was confirmed that Hong Kong will host the second edition of the tournament, from October 7 to 12, 2024.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5-world-cup] On the eve of the tournament, it was announced that future editions will have 16 teams (split into four groups) and play 56 games total.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5-world-cup] In October 2024 it was announced that Rome will host the 2026 tournament.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5-world-cup] The 16 countries play a total of 56 games over four or five days.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5-world-cup] Each team has five active players and eight players total on the roster, with the mixed-gender nature of the tournament requiring teams to have half of their roster to be of each gender, and at least two active players per gender in the game.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5-world-cup] Players must be a minimum of 15 years old during the calendar year of the tournament.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] Outs (eliminations) occur either when a hit ball is caught before it touches the ground by a defender, or (in specific situations) when a defender with the ball either touches the base a runner is supposed to reach, or touches the runner themselves.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] Offensive players can also get themselves out by breaking the rules while hitting the ball or running the bases.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] The teams switch roles after three outs are made, with an "inning" being completed when both teams have played offense once.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] The game is played to five innings, with any ties being broken by playing extra innings as necessary, and games generally lasting 15 to 20 minutes.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] Oftentimes, a best-of-three (or even best-of-five) series of "sets" is played to determine the result of a matchup between two teams.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] Unlike baseball/softball, there is no pitcher, with the batter (offensive player who hits the ball) starting each play with the ball, which is the only equipment used in the game.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] The WBSC proposed the game in 2017 with the intention of growing baseball/softball on a global level, claiming that the game's low cost, fast pace, and small field make it a more accessible and appealing entry point to those sports.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] It organizes a mixed-gender B5 World Cup for senior and youth players in alternating years, with teams required to field at least two active players per gender.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] The game is also scheduled to be played in a mixed-gender format at the 2026 Summer Youth Olympics, and has started to find adoption in schools, national championships, and other international events around the world.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] B5 was inspired by similar games that have been played on the streets in Latin America and elsewhere for decades, such as cuatro esquinas (*four corners*) in Cuba and pelotica de goma (*little rubber ball*) in Venezuela.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] In some cases, B5 significantly diverges from the rules of these games; for example, it does not feature a pitcher, as is done in one street variation in Colombia, and players are allowed to run the bases, as opposed to only walking, as is required in one version of "cuatro esquinas".
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] Before B5, the WBSC had tried promoting several other baseball variants at a youth level, such as tee-ball, without significant success.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] B5 was invented in part to increase the odds that a sport similar to baseball and softball will be played in the Olympics, with B5 meant to contribute to an ultimate goal of having a billion fans in the baseball-softball community by 2030 and helping to demonstrate the global reach of the games.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] It also intended to create a game that would be more accessible and cheap, as the only equipment used in B5 is the rubber ball, and the field is much smaller than a baseball diamond or softball field, with the game being playable indoors.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] In this respect, as well as the fact that there are fewer players required to play a game, B5 is meant to imitate smaller, more urban variants of other major sports, such as 3x3 basketball, futsal, and rugby sevens.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] Inclusiveness is meant to be another goal of B5, with the game being scheduled to be the first mixed-gender team sport in an Olympic event to not have a separate competition for male-only or female-only teams.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] In addition, the game is meant to be simpler to learn, have more youth appeal, and be more exciting, with players participating more frequently throughout the game.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] Another claimed benefit is that with B5 being introduced across the entire world at the same time, no one country is likely to dominate the game; the lack of the pitcher role, which is highly specialized, contributes to this.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] The first Baseball5 international competition took place at Foro Italico, Italy in 2018.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] The game was demonstrated and played in various places across the world, such as in the United States during the MLB All-Star Week, in the 2021 Bulgarian Olympic Festival, and on the sidelines of the 2018 Summer Youth Olympics in Argentina and the 2020 Summer Paralympics in Japan.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] The WBSC has tried to promote B5 for socially beneficial purposes as well, by taking it to places such as Jordan's Azraq refugee camp.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] It is being implemented in many schools in some countries, like Australia and France, and is now played in 83 countries.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] In 2025, the WBSC celebrated May 5th (5/5) as "High5 for Baseball5" day.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] Before the 2022 Baseball5 World Cup, a new B5 rulebook was published that increased clarity on some of the rules, as well as changing some of the field dimensions.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] For example, the bases were increased in size from 50 cm (20 in) to 60 cm (24 in), and were moved from the inner edge of the infield to the outer edge, increasing the distance between them by 0.5 metres (1 ft 8 in).
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] In 2025, a double base was added for home plate.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] The infield is a 13 m (42.65 ft)-square, with a base in every corner.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] The fair territory is a 18 m (59.06 ft)-square, with one of the corners coinciding with the home plate (the final base).
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] The batter's box is a 3 m (9.84 ft)-square.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] It is placed outside of the fair territory and is built on the extension of the two foul lines (which distinguish fair and foul territory, and sit in fair territory) crossing each other at the home plate corner; the lines are included as part of the batter's box area.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] All bases are marked on the ground (i.e. they are not physical cushions like in baseball/softball).
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] Ideal shape and size of the first three bases is a 60 cm (23.62 in)-square, and they are placed in the outfield (the part of fair territory outside of the infield).
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] In order to avoid collisions, the first base is "doubled" in foul territory, with the outer base referred to as the "safety base".
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] Home plate also has a double base, known as the "safety plate", which can be found diagonally adjacent in the batter's box as a 90 cm (35 in) triangle.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] The ideal height of the fences bounding the field is 1 m (3.28 ft).
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] However, every league or tournament organisation may decide on other ways of limiting the field of play, such as using existing walls or marking the ground with lines.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] The only piece of equipment used is a hollow rubber ball with a circumference of 208.4 mm (8.20 in).
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] The Visitor team starts the game in offense, with the Home team on defense.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] The goal of the offensive team is to have each of its players hit the ball and then run counterclockwise around all four bases in order without being eliminated by the defense, thus scoring one run for their team.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] The act of hitting takes place while a hitter is entirely in the batter's box; the hitter must not step out of the lines until the hit ball reaches fair territory, and must first signal which hand they will hit with.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] If these requirements are not met, or if the ball goes into foul territory before passing first or third base, then the batter is out.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] The batter in the action of running towards first base, after putting the ball in play, has to touch the base in foul territory (the "safety base") except in circumstances where a collision could be avoided by going toward the base in fair territory.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] A runner (offensive player) who touches first base, second base, third base and home plate in that order scores one run for their team, and then leaves the field until their next turn as a hitter.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] When scoring, a runner must step on the safety plate rather than home plate, which is reserved for the defenders in order to avoid collisions.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] Note: If a play occurs where the batter failed to legally hit the ball, then the play is canceled (i.e. any runners who got out or advanced around the bases during the play return to their bases as if the play never happened) and the batter is eliminated.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] In teams with only five players, the first player "called out" (eliminated) in that inning becomes pinch runner on the base of the runner who is required to hit.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] The batting order and the gender balance (in mixed-gender competitions) shall always be respected.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] The five players (1st Base, 2nd Base, Midfielder, Shortstop, and 3rd Base, from right to left) of the defensive team shall all be in fair territory when the batter hits the ball.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] The ball remains live if a defender with the ball leaves the field, so long as they secured possession of the ball in fair territory.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] If the ball leaves the court due to a defensive error (missed throw or missed catch of a thrown ball), each runner is awarded an extra base (i.e. the batter goes to 2nd base, and all other runners advance 2 bases as well).
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] Any runner who clearly advanced 2 bases before the defensive error may be granted an extra base as well (i.e. a runner on 1st who advanced to 3rd before the error can be awarded home plate).
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] The game ends at the end of the fifth inning if one team has scored more runs than the opponent.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] Should the Home Team be ahead on the score after the Guest Team has completed its fifth offensive inning, the game is over and the Home Team wins.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] Many B5 tournaments feature best-of-three series known as "matches" or "games", with each individual game in the series called a "game" or "set", and the team winning two sets being the winner of the overall match.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] In case of a tie game, the teams shall play and complete extra inning(s) until one team scores more runs than the opponent.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] In the sixth inning, the player scheduled to hit fifth (i.e. the player who batted last in the fifth inning, and whose name precedes the first batter of the sixth inning) is placed on first base as a runner to start the inning.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] In the seventh inning, the players scheduled to hit fifth and fourth are placed on first and second base respectively, and so on with three runners to start the following innings until the game ends.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] By WBSC regulations, the game ends if there is still a tie after 7 extra innings.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] A game is over if a team leads by 15 runs at the end of the third inning or by 10 at the end of the fourth.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] At the international level, B5 is administered by the World Baseball Softball Confederation (WBSC).
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] Within each country, it is administered by the national baseball and/or softball governing body.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] Exceptions apply for certain countries, such as Japan, where a specific governing body has been set up to run B5.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] The Baseball5 World Cup (B5WC) and Youth Baseball5 World Cup (YB5WC) are administered by the WBSC, with both tournaments alternating and happening every two years, and following the general format of having 50 games played between 12 national teams over 7 days.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] Continental qualifiers for each tournament will be played during their off-year.
[src:2022-baseball5-world-cup/baseball5] The 2025 YB5WC will act as a qualifier for the mixed-gender Baseball5 event to be held in the Dakar 2026 Youth Olympic Games (YOG).
